CatDescriptText: Helen Jones, housewife, 7237 Hermitage Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 11, 1959, pg. A1, with question: "Do you believe churches of any denomination receive appreciation financial help from racketeers?" Answer reads: "I don't know about Pittsburgh because I've only been here a short while. However, in Zanesville, Ohio where I lived previously, the churches were supported by church members, good church members, and no racketeers."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Helen Jones wearing houndstooth coat and head scarf, standing in front of brick wall
